About a dozen children were injured when the taxi transporting them to school collided with a car and rolled down an embankment on Wednesday morning.Rescue Care s Garrith Jamieson said 20 people were injured when the taxi and light motor vehicle crashed on the M1 near the Old Richmond Road in KwaZulu-Natal. The 20 patients of which 12 were school children between the ages of 10 and 15 were transported to hospital for further treatment. 